captions.text:
-(narrator) How far would you go
to take care of those you love,

to make sure that
they remain healthy?

-(radio) You've just been listening
to Sounds of Silverwood.

-(man)
This is such a bad idea.

-Pfft-heh, it's a little late for that,
don't you think?

-Look, let's just
drive back down the mountain.

We'll find a nice hotel
and stay for the whole weekend.

I don't know, I just
don't want them to ruin it all.

-C'mon baby,
they can't be that bad.

-(elder) There she is!
-(woman) Hi! I'm Melony.

-Whoop, too late.
That's how Mark got born.

Hello, Mark.
She's a lot prettier than you said.
Come here, give me a hug.

-Hi, Mrs. Williams.
It's nice to meet you.

-So, I gotta get back in the kitchen
and finish up dinner.

Figured you guys would
get upstairs to the guest room.

Odd fact:
I don't usually eat red meat,

-What? No, just,
if you give it a little chance--

-Okay, let's see if
he's gonna feed me-- oh!

Okay you're feeding me,
that's happening.

of part one of this week's
BlackBoxTV episode.

Click anywhere to
watch the conclusion.

Mobile devices, please use
the links in the description below.

I think the biggest problem of horror films is that they are so long so it 
demands a terrible plot, but blackbox seems to acknowledge that by making 
short, scary videos with about as much as plot as necessary. They don't 
drag you along. You can just watch one video and choose to enhance the 
experience by watching more. The atmosphere, editing, etc. is really good. 
Keep it up guys!
